ABUJA – The Federal Government yesterday gave a grant of N25 million to five institutions in Abuja as a token of appreciation for their contributions to national development. The institutions or academies that received the grants include Nigerian Academy of Science, Nigerian Academy of Engineering, Nigerian Academy of Letters, the Nigerian Academy of Education and the Nigerian Academy of Social Science.Each of these institutions received N5 million. Dr. Ogbonnaya Onu, Minister of Science and Technology, speaking while disbursing the grants to the beneficiaries, tasked the Academies to work in synergy with government and apply their knowledge to solve numerous challenges facing the nation. He charged them to key into the fight against corruption, insecurity and myriads of challenges confronting the economy, adding that these plethora of challenges would only be surmounted with the application of knowledge-driven technology and innovation. He described the Academies as reservoirs of knowledge, which could be of great benefit to the nation in her bid to achieve greatness. Onu contended that for Nigeria to overcome her challenges knowledge and hard work of people must be appreciated and rewarded to encourage them to do more, adding that by so doing, Nigeria would eventually join the comity of developed nations. He pointed out that only the best minds, ideas and innovations are good for Nigeria, assuring that when the Ministry’s funding improves, more capital would be injected to fund their research activities. He, however, advised them to make judicious use of the grants in the best interest of the nation. Speaking on behalf of the recipients, Prof. Fola Lasisi, the President of the Nigerian Academy of Engineering, expressed his profound appreciation to the Ministry for blazing the trail in the search for knowledge- driven technology in the country. Lasisi, promised on behalf of the other academies to make judicious use of the grants.